An inequality with a quadratic expression on one side and zero on the other side, is called a quadratic inequality in one variable. For example, 2x2 + 7x – 4 < 0 and (x + 1)((x – 3) . 0 are quadratic inequalities in one variable, x. 
To solve a quadratic inequality as (x + 1)(x – 3) . 0, we have to find the range of values of x so that the expression on the left is greater than zero.
The three methods which can be used to solve a quadratic inequality are graph sketching, number line and table methods.
